Filmed at Roman ruins, Sabratha, Libya

During the British retreat in North Africa in World War Two a British Army captain, David Holland, takes shelter with a Bedouin tribe and marries the sheik's daughter. Ten years later Holland's younger brother Charles, is informed that David may still be alive in Libya and sets out to find him.
